Interactive pty harnesses
=========================

The harnesses here drive shit through a pseudo-terminal, so they cover the
job-control and signal behavior that needs a real controlling terminal. They are
run by hand rather than wired into make test, since the defects they guard are
timing-based and a golden cannot capture them. Each prints PASS or FAIL and exits
with a matching status.

Build the debug binary first with `make -C src MODE=dbg`, then run a harness with
its path or let it default to ../../shit-dbg.

mimic_terminal_handoff.py
    Runs a mimicked foreground command in an interactive session whose terminal
    has TOSTOP enabled, and checks that the job completes and the prompt returns.
    It guards the fork synchronization in src/Utils.cpp, where the child blocks on
    a pipe until the parent hands over the controlling terminal.
